questions.question:
Consider the DFA M1 = (Q, Sigma, delta, F) and NFA M2 as defined below. Let the language accepted by machine M1 be L. What language does machine M2 accept, if:
i.   F2 = A^c
ii.  F2 = L^c
iii. F2 = L
iv.  F2 = L^2

Where,
Q2 := {Q x Q | Q} union {q_0}
delta_2(qe, r) = {(p, q, r) | q in Q}
delta_2((p, q), r) = {(p, q', r) | q' in delta(q, r)}
A = {(p, q, r) | q in Q and p in F}
B = {(p, q, r) | p in Q, q in F2, r in Sigma*}
C = {(p, q, r) | p in Q, q in F2, r in Sigma*}
D = {(p, q, r) | p in Q, q in Q, r in Sigma*, (p, q) in F2}
